  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Using a reference object with Reality Composer Pro"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can use reference objects in your visionOS app to track real-world objects in a person’s surroundings.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "With this capability, you can attach virtual content to those real-world objects to create engaging experiences.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For example, with a reference object, you can track a household item and add virtual content to it, like highlighting a part and showing how to fix it.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To create a reference object, first, you obtain a 3D model asset, train a machine learning model with that 3D model asset in Create ML, and then import the resulting reference object file into your app.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "With Reality Composer Pro, you can set up object tracking by using the reference object file as an anchor entity to track your real-world object in your app.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For more information about creating a reference object file, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.visionOS/documentation/visionOS/implementing-object-tracking-in-your-visionOS-app",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Set-up-a-scene-in-Reality-Composer-Pro",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Set up a scene in Reality Composer Pro",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can use Reality Composer Pro to import your reference object file and set up it up for tracking.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "However, before importing your reference object file, you need to set up a scene in Reality Composer Pro by following these steps:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Create a project in Xcode using the visionOS app template.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "When choosing options for your project, be sure to choose the RealityKit option from the Immersive Space Renderer pop-up menu to configure an immersive space.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Select the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "Package",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " file with the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": ".realitycomposerpro",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " extension in the Project navigator on the left.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Click the Open in Reality Composer Pro button at the top right of the 3D View.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "When Reality Composer Pro opens, delete both default spheres and the grid material in the Scene navigator on the left to begin with an empty scene.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "package-and-rcp",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-an-anchor-entity",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create an anchor entity",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After creating an empty scene, you need to create an anchor entity for your reference object.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "This allows you to track the real-word object and attach virtual content to it.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Start by clicking the Add button (+) at the bottom of the Scene navigator on the left and choosing Transform from the menu.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-transform",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To add anchoring behavior to the entity, you need to add a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/realitykit/component",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Click the Add Component button at the bottom of the inspector area to the right of the 3D View.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "From the list of available components that appears, double-click the Anchoring option. The Anchoring component appears in the inspector area for the entity.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-anchoring",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The Anchoring component requires a target to tether the anchor entity to.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Because you’re tracking an object within your app, click the Target pop-up button for the Anchoring component and choose Object from the menu.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-anchoring-object",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To import your reference object file, click the Anchor Object button for the Anchoring component, navigate to the file, and click Select.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "importing-reference-object",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After importing your reference object file, a semitransparent model of it appears in the 3D View.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "You can use this ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "visual cue",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " as a guide to place virtual content precisely on top of the real object.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can move the visual cue away from the origin by moving an ancestor entity of the entity with the Anchoring component.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "This is particularly helpful when you have multiple entities acting as object anchors, which might cause the visual cues to overlap at the origin.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "reference-object-model",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To get the anchor’s position in the real world (an anchor transform) during tracking, you need to configure a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpatialTrackingSession",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " using RealityKit.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/realitykit/spatialtrackingsession/",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
